      "content": "It's a heavy burden to carry, but letting go isn't the answer. Your health may be declining, but you're still a vital part of their lives. Your struggles are theirs too, in a different way. They can't just leave you behind; they're attached to you. Maybe it's time to find new ways to support each other, to find balance. Remember, it's okay to ask for help, and it's okay to lean on others. You're not a problem; you're a family member.",
